article.headline: Franklin Pierce 70, New Hampshire 69 (OT)
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Darryl Minnifield scored a team-high 17 points and Marcus Wellman added 15 as Franklin Pierce beat New Hampshire 70-69 in overtime Tuesday. Timothy Munch and Nazim Senaldi added 12 points each for Franklin Pierce (1-0). Franklin Pierce scored first in overtime. After a free throw miss by Raven guard Jack Barrett, New Hampshire's Tyrece Gibbs scored a 3-pointer to bring the Wildcats (0-2) one point behind, 68-67. Senaldi put Franklin Pierce up 70-67 with seven seconds left. UNH's Jude Roybal raced down the court and threw a long-distance shot that went through the net as time expired, but it was just shy of a 3-pointer. UNH led 32-31 at halftime. Mike Christensen tied a career-high 22 points for UNH and Blagoj Janev scored 17 points and eight rebounds.
